OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,423,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1780168284
OL,3,CCannibal killer refused parole for
OL,4,Cninth time
OL,6,FIt emerged Harker had told friends and
OL,7,Fpsychiatrists that he had fried part
OL,8,Fof her thigh and eaten it with pasta
OL,9,Fand cheese.
OL,11,FHe has been eligible for parole since
OL,12,F2013 and this month a ninth hearing
OL,13,Fwas held to determine whether he
OL,14,Fshould be freed or sent to an open
OL,15,Fprison.
OL,17,FThe Parole Board said it was still not
OL,18,Fconsidered safe to allow him to be
OL,19,Freleased or to be transferred, based
OL,20,Fon the continuing need to protect the
OL,21,Fpublic.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,423,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1780168284
OL,3,CCannibal killer refused parole for
OL,4,Cninth time
OL,6,FHarker was 24 when he was sentenced in
OL,7,F1999. Psychiatrists agreed he had a
OL,8,Fsevere psychopathic disorder when he
OL,9,Fkilled Ms Paterson, meaning he was not
OL,10,Fguilty of murder.
OL,12,FThe Parole Board said the law required
OL,13,FHarker's case to be assessed regularly.
OL,15,FA report into his recent behaviour
OL,16,Ffound that his behaviour in custody
OL,17,Fhad "significantly improved", with no
OL,18,Fdisciplinary findings since 2015.
OL,26,@yD@EOUyD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/7
